      <byline class="print_byline">By Paul Meller (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Meller, Paul</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Belgian court sentences pastor Andras Pandy to life imprisonment and his daughter Agnes to 21 years for murdering most of their family (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a macabre case that has gripped Belgium, a Hungarian-born pastor was sentenced to life imprisonment and his daughter to 21 years for having murdered most of their family. Andras Pandy, 74, was found guilty of murdering two wives and four of his children, and of raping three of his daughters. His eldest daughter Agnes, 44, was found guilty of helping to kill her mother, her stepmother, two brothers and one sister.</p>
        <p>Paul Meller (NYT)</p>
      </block>
